---

import Verticalgrid from "../assets/VerticalGrid.astro";
---

<section aria-labelledby="Featurethree" id="Featurethree " class="relative">
  <Verticalgrid />
  <div class="max-w-7xl px-8 md:px-12 lg:px-32 mx-auto py-12 lg:py-24 relative">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto lg:text-center">
      <div>
        <span
          class="text-transparent bg-clip-text font-medium tracking-widest bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-400 via-teal-500 to-indigo-500 text-xs uppercase"
          >Project Generation</span
        ><p class="text-3xl mt-8 font-normal text-white">
            Experience clean, optimized, and conflict-free Xcode projects for effortless maintenance and streamlined development.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <ul
      class="grid grid-cols-2 lg:text-center gap-6 mt-12 list-none lg:grid-cols-4 lg:gap-12 lg:mt-24"
      role="list">
      <li>
        <div>
          <p class="text-lg font-medium text-white lg:text-xl">
            Zero Git conflicts
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-base text-slate-400">
          By generating projects on demand, you can avoid the need to include them in the Git repository, eliminating the risk of merge conflicts.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div>
          <p class="text-lg font-medium text-white lg:text-xl">Focused projects</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-base text-slate-400">
          Simply specify your focused targets, and we'll perform a thorough tree-shaking of the project graph. The result? A lightning-fast Xcode experience.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div>
          <p class="text-lg font-medium text-white lg:text-xl">
            Linting
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-base text-slate-400">
          Frustrating errors that would otherwise be caught at build time are now caught at generation time.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div>
          <p class="text-lg font-medium text-white lg:text-xl">
            Swift-based DSL
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-base text-slate-400">
          Leverage Swift and Xcode to describe projects, create custom abstractions, and easily share code components.          
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
